%F A197630 a(n) = ((Sum_{k=1..p-1} k^(p-1)) - p - (p-1)!)/p^2, where p is the n-th prime and n >= 2.
%e A197630 a(3) = 13 because the 3rd prime is 5 and ((Sum_{k=1..4} q_5(k)) - w_5)/5 = (0 + 3 + 16 + 51 - 5)/5 = 13.
